This implementation is a functional reference. Do not use it in production without completing the hardening steps below.

1. Callback Authenticity
The callback endpoint /_functions/focasCallback is public. Without token validation, a malicious actor could forge callback requests and mark orders as paid without a real payment.
Before production, verify all of the following in the callback handler:

The pending order (lidm) exists in FocasPendingOrders
The order status is not already PAID (prevent duplicate processing)
The returned authAmt matches the original purchAmt
The returned merID matches your own merchant ID
The respToken is valid, if token verification is enabled by the bank


2. reqToken / respToken Validation
If First Bank enables FOCAS parameter verification for your account, implement:

reqToken — sent with the payment request to FOCAS
respToken — returned in the callback from FOCAS

Do not commit the verification key or token secret to GitHub.
Use a placeholder in code:
jsconst FOCAS_VERIFY_KEY = "YOUR_FOCAS_VERIFY_KEY"; // replace before production

3. Amount Matching
Before marking an order as PAID, always compare:

focasParams.purchAmt — the original amount stored in FocasPendingOrders
authAmt — the amount returned in the FOCAS callback

They must match exactly. If they differ, do not mark the order as paid and log the discrepancy.

4. Duplicate Callback Protection
FOCAS may retry a callback if it does not receive a valid response.
Before calling submitEvent(), check:

Is the pending order already PAID?
Is submitEventStatus already SUBMITTED?

If either is true, skip the submitEvent() call to avoid duplicate order updates.

5. CMS Permissions
Do not allow public users to write to payment collections in production.
Recommended permissions for both FocasPendingOrders and FocasOrders:
PermissionSettingReadAdminCreateAdminUpdateAdminDeleteAdmin
The backend uses { suppressAuth: true } so Velo backend code can still write to these collections without requiring public access.

6. Sensitive Data — Do Not Store or Commit
Never store or commit any of the following:

Full card numbers (pan) — remove from FocasOrders before production
Bank backend account credentials
reqToken verification parameters or secrets
Raw production payment callbacks
Production transaction CSV exports
Real MerchantID, TerminalID, or merID values


7. Logging
Debug logs are useful during development. In production:

Do not log full callback bodies containing card data
Do not log merchant credentials
Remove or gate all console.log calls that expose transaction details before going live
